---
import FinancialDisclaimer from '@/components/layout/financial-disclaimer.astro';
import DefaultLayout from '@/layouts/DefaultLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'April 12, 2026';
---

<DefaultLayout
  title="Disclaimer — FirstHomeGuide.ca"
  description="Important disclaimers about the educational content, calculators, and tools on FirstHomeGuide.ca."
>
  <section class="section-padding container max-w-3xl">
    <p class="text-muted-foreground text-sm">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    <h1 class="mt-2 text-4xxl leading-tight tracking-tight md:text-5xl">
      Disclaimer
    </h1>
    <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-4 leading-relaxed">
      FirstHomeGuide.ca is a free educational resource. The disclaimer below applies to all
      content, tools, calculators, and resources on the Site.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-8">
      <FinancialDisclaimer variant="full" />
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-8 text-sm leading-relaxed md:text-base">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Calculator assumptions</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Our calculators use published formulas (CMHC premium tiers, stress test rate, GDS/TDS
          ratios, provincial land transfer tax rates, etc.) that were accurate when last
          reviewed. Results are estimates only. Your actual qualification, rate, and total
          cost depend on factors no calculator can capture — your full credit profile,
          lender-specific underwriting, property-specific charges, and changes in government
          policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Provincial and territorial differences</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Home-buying rules vary significantly across Canada&rsquo;s provinces and territories —
          land transfer tax, first-time-buyer rebates, closing process, legal requirements, and
          consumer-protection rules all differ. We note major differences where we can. Always
          confirm provincial or territorial rules with a local lawyer, realtor, or mortgage
          professional.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Affiliate and sponsorship disclosure</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          FirstHomeGuide.ca is operated by LendCity (FSRA Brokerage Licence #12728). When you
          book a call through the Site, you are connected with a licensed mortgage
          professional at LendCity. Editorial content is created independently of any
          commercial relationship; program coverage is not conditional on a lender being a
          LendCity partner.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">No professional relationship</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Reading this site, using a tool, or booking a call does not create a mortgage-broker,
          lawyer-client, or fiduciary relationship. A formal relationship begins only when you
          sign an engagement agreement with a licensed professional.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</DefaultLayout>
